744
00:48:35,489 --> 00:48:36,740
Got another code 12.

745
00:48:36,823 --> 00:48:37,908
Name?

746
00:48:37,991 --> 00:48:39,034
Collins. Christine.

747
00:48:39,117 --> 00:48:40,577
No, no, no, listen,
this is a mistake.

748
00:48:40,660 --> 00:48:41,912
Certifying officer?

749
00:48:41,995 --> 00:48:44,456
Captain J.J. Jones,
Lincoln Heights Division.

750
00:48:44,539 --> 00:48:46,541
No, no, please! Please! The
police are trying to punish me...

751
00:48:46,625 --> 00:48:48,709
If you keep it up, I'm gonna
have to put you in a straitjacket.

752
00:48:48,793 --> 00:48:50,044
Do you want that?

753
00:48:50,127 --> 00:48:51,170
No, ma'am.

754
00:48:51,253 --> 00:48:53,672
Then behave yourself.
Code 12.

755
00:48:54,715 --> 00:48:56,342
I'm not mad!

756
00:48:56,425 --> 00:48:57,802
Please.

757
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:00,930
Oh, God.

758
00:49:01,013 --> 00:49:02,348
All right.

759
00:49:07,603 --> 00:49:08,854
No!

760
00:49:17,780 --> 00:49:18,989
Stop!

761
00:49:25,204 --> 00:49:26,831
Spread your legs.

762
00:49:27,414 --> 00:49:28,499
What?

763
00:49:32,044 --> 00:49:33,546
Wider.

764
00:49:33,587 --> 00:49:35,214
Oh.

765
00:49:46,057 --> 00:49:48,893
I'm not sick!

766
00:49:55,442 --> 00:49:56,609
Touch me! Touch me!

767
00:49:58,611 --> 00:50:01,156
Inside. This is your room.

768
00:50:01,239 --> 00:50:03,324
The doctor has left for the day.
He will see you in the morning.

769
00:50:03,408 --> 00:50:05,743
Can I... I need to speak
to somebody in authority.

770
00:50:05,827 --> 00:50:06,953
Sorry.

771
00:50:07,036 --> 00:50:11,708
My room! No. No, no,
no, this is my room.

772
00:50:12,083 --> 00:50:13,126
Can I make
a phone call?

773
00:50:13,209 --> 00:50:15,170
Phone privileges are
earned by good behavior.

774
00:50:15,253 --> 00:50:18,965
You're not allowed newspapers,
magazines, radio, books or sharp objects.

775
00:50:19,048 --> 00:50:20,467
This is for your own good.
Help me!

776
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:22,135
Listen to me.

777
00:50:22,218 --> 00:50:24,053
My room.

778
00:50:24,095 --> 00:50:26,806
No,
this is my room.

779
00:50:27,307 --> 00:50:29,142
Oh, God!

780
00:50:29,225 --> 00:50:30,518
My room.

781
00:50:32,061 --> 00:50:35,190
No, no,
this is my room.

782
00:50:37,566 --> 00:50:39,401
My room.

783
00:50:40,903 --> 00:50:45,032
My room! My room!
My room!

784
00:50:45,324 --> 00:50:47,534
My room!

785
00:50:47,618 --> 00:50:50,496
They said it was my room!

786
00:51:02,591 --> 00:51:04,510
You have a problem?

787
00:51:04,593 --> 00:51:07,971
Overheated, that's all.
She'll be fine in a bit.

788
00:51:09,306 --> 00:51:10,808
Hey, listen, could
you give me a hand?

789
00:51:10,891 --> 00:51:14,686
I'm trying to find a place called
the Northcott Ranch, up by Wineville.

790
00:51:16,146 --> 00:51:17,981
Northcott Ranch, huh?

791
00:51:21,235 --> 00:51:24,530
Oh, yeah, yeah.

792
00:51:24,988 --> 00:51:27,699
You're almost there.

793
00:51:27,783 --> 00:51:31,285
You just... You just
follow this road west,

794
00:51:31,369 --> 00:51:33,996
about two, no, three miles.

795
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,624
And then you take
that next right.

796
00:51:36,666 --> 00:51:40,128
And you stay on that and it
will bring you right to it.

797
00:51:42,672 --> 00:51:45,007
Is something going
on out there?

798
00:51:45,091 --> 00:51:46,217
No.

799
00:51:46,300 --> 00:51:48,469
Just looking into
a juvenile matter.

800
00:51:49,679 --> 00:51:50,847
Thanks for your help.

801
00:51:50,930 --> 00:51:52,140
Sure.

802
00:52:39,060 --> 00:52:40,187
Hello?

803
00:53:25,856 --> 00:53:27,942
Hey!

804
00:53:28,025 --> 00:53:30,444
Hey! Hey!

805
00:53:30,528 --> 00:53:33,572
Come here!
Come here!

806
00:53:39,120 --> 00:53:40,830
This is the police!

807
00:53:40,913 --> 00:53:44,083
I have a warrant for a
minor named Sanford Clark.

808
00:53:45,626 --> 00:53:47,753
Open the door
or stand aside.

809
00:55:01,075 --> 00:55:02,493
Hey! Stop!

810
00:55:03,577 --> 00:55:06,830
Stop! Stop it! Stop it!

811
00:55:06,914 --> 00:55:10,000
Stop it! Stop it or I'll push
your face through this floor!

812
00:55:10,042 --> 00:55:11,126
Stop it!

813
00:55:11,210 --> 00:55:12,252
Fine!

814
00:55:12,795 --> 00:55:14,713
Give me your hands.

815
00:55:24,306 --> 00:55:25,974
Come on.
Sit down.

816
00:55:27,518 --> 00:55:28,769
Jesus!

817
00:55:30,395 --> 00:55:31,855
What the hell is
wrong with you, kid?

818
00:55:31,897 --> 00:55:33,357
Huh?

819
00:55:33,398 --> 00:55:35,275
Don't you know assaulting
a cop is against the law?

820
00:55:35,359 --> 00:55:37,528
What difference
does it make?

821
00:55:39,154 --> 00:55:41,782
We're just sending you
back to Canada, son.

822
00:55:41,865 --> 00:55:44,034
It isn't the end
of the world.

823
00:55:44,660 --> 00:55:45,869
What?

824
00:55:47,788 --> 00:55:51,500
Well, you can't stay in the
U.S. As long as you want, pal.

825
00:55:56,212 --> 00:55:57,797
No word from Mrs. Collins?

826
00:55:57,880 --> 00:55:59,257
We haven't heard from her.

827
00:55:59,298 --> 00:56:01,509
Get on down to her house,
make sure she's all right.

828
00:56:01,592 --> 00:56:03,052
And if she's not there,
check with her neighbors.

829
00:56:03,136 --> 00:56:04,220
Find out what they know.

830
00:56:04,262 --> 00:56:05,346
Absolutely.

831
00:56:05,430 --> 00:56:08,474
<i>And now KGF welcomes the
Reverend Gustav Briegleb</i>

832
00:56:08,558 --> 00:56:10,726
<i>of St. Paul's Presbyterian.</i>

833
00:56:10,810 --> 00:56:15,189
This is Pastor Gustav A. Briegleb
of St. Paul's Presbyterian Church,

834
00:56:15,273 --> 00:56:18,109
bringing you the Lord's
word on Radio KGF.

835
00:56:18,192 --> 00:56:19,861
Good evening.

836
00:56:19,944 --> 00:56:21,863
I had hoped to have
a guest with us tonight,

837
00:56:21,946 --> 00:56:24,240
but apparently
she has been delayed.

838
00:56:24,282 --> 00:56:28,244
<i>And since she cannot be here to tell you
what she told the press this afternoon,</i>

839
00:56:28,327 --> 00:56:30,955
<i>I'll have to fill in
as best I can.</i>

840
00:56:31,038 --> 00:56:32,790
<i>I'm going to tell
you what happened</i>

841
00:56:32,874 --> 00:56:37,128
<i>and I'm going to keep on telling
you every night, right here,</i>

842
00:56:37,211 --> 00:56:40,256
<i>until somebody does
something about it.</i>

843
00:56:44,051 --> 00:56:47,138
<i>The Desert Local,
train number 45,</i>

844
00:56:47,221 --> 00:56:50,515
<i>will be arriving on
track two in five minutes.</i>

845
00:56:51,141 --> 00:56:53,226
Hello. I'd like a
ticket to Canada.

846
00:56:53,310 --> 00:56:55,520
Alberta or Vancouver,
whatever's leaving tonight.

847
00:56:55,604 --> 00:56:57,564
I don't have anything
going that far tonight.

848
00:56:57,647 --> 00:56:59,858
The best I can do is put
you on a train to Seattle.

849
00:56:59,941 --> 00:57:02,694
From there you can transfer to a
local or drive across the border.

850
00:57:02,778 --> 00:57:04,154
That would be fine.

851
00:57:04,237 --> 00:57:05,447
Roundtrip?

852
00:57:05,489 --> 00:57:06,656
One way.

853
00:57:06,740 --> 00:57:08,158
That'll be $15.

854
00:57:08,241 --> 00:57:09,284
Right.

855
00:57:12,913 --> 00:57:14,539
There you go.

856
00:57:14,623 --> 00:57:16,124
Thank you. There you
go. Enjoy your trip.

857
00:57:16,208 --> 00:57:17,417
I will.

858
00:57:35,018 --> 00:57:37,062
Breakfast is half an hour.

859
00:57:41,691 --> 00:57:44,026
Please, miss, I need to
see a doctor in charge.

860
00:57:44,068 --> 00:57:45,528
The dining room
is down the hall.

861
00:57:45,611 --> 00:57:48,531
The doctor will call
for you when he's ready.

862
00:58:00,501 --> 00:58:02,670
Do you want
eggs or oatmeal?

863
00:58:04,547 --> 00:58:06,173
Okay, that's everyone
that's here.

864
00:58:06,257 --> 00:58:07,633
All right.

865
00:58:07,716 --> 00:58:09,552
You can pull the oatmeal.

866
00:58:09,635 --> 00:58:11,011
Do you want
it for tomorrow?

867
00:58:11,053 --> 00:58:12,430
You know, just dump it. All right.

868
00:58:12,513 --> 00:58:14,014
You should eat.

869
00:58:15,015 --> 00:58:16,809
Eating is normal.

870
00:58:16,892 --> 00:58:19,687
You gotta do everything
you can to look normal.

871
00:58:19,728 --> 00:58:21,230
It's the only chance
you got.

872
00:58:21,272 --> 00:58:22,440
I'm not hungry.

873
00:58:22,523 --> 00:58:24,775
Barbara, you have to
eat now. I'm not hungry.

874
00:58:24,859 --> 00:58:27,361
My name's Carol Dexter.
What's yours?

875
00:58:28,070 --> 00:58:29,989
Christine.
Christine Collins.

876
00:58:32,032 --> 00:58:34,201
Now, finish it all. I know
it's hard, but you gotta try.

877
00:58:34,285 --> 00:58:35,577
Oh, boy.

878
00:58:42,417 --> 00:58:44,210
I heard them talking.

879
00:58:44,294 --> 00:58:46,337
You're here on code 12?

880
00:58:46,421 --> 00:58:48,047
Police action.

881
00:58:48,131 --> 00:58:49,674
I mean, the doctors,
the staff, they figure

882
00:58:49,758 --> 00:58:51,092
that if the police
brought you here,

883
00:58:51,134 --> 00:58:53,178
there must be
a good reason for it.

884
00:58:53,261 --> 00:58:55,638
There isn't a good
reason for it.

885
00:58:56,139 --> 00:58:59,392
I'm perfectly sane and I
will explain that to them.

886
00:59:00,101 --> 00:59:01,186
How?

887
00:59:02,312 --> 00:59:06,065
The more you try to act sane,
the crazier you start to look.

888
00:59:06,107 --> 00:59:09,944
If you smile too much, you're
delusional or you're stifling hysteria.

889
00:59:10,028 --> 00:59:12,781
And if you don't smile,
you're depressed.

890
00:59:12,864 --> 00:59:17,410
If you remain neutral, you're emotionally
withdrawn, potentially catatonic.

891
00:59:21,122 --> 00:59:22,957
You've given this
a lot of thought.

892
00:59:22,999 --> 00:59:25,668
Yeah, I have.
Don't you get it?

893
00:59:26,503 --> 00:59:28,921
You're a code 12,
so am I.

894
00:59:28,962 --> 00:59:31,173
We're here for the
exact same reasons.

895
00:59:31,256 --> 00:59:33,383
We both pissed
off the cops.

896
00:59:34,468 --> 00:59:37,387
Now, you see, you
see that lady there?

897
00:59:37,471 --> 00:59:39,890
She was married to a cop
who kept beating her up.

898
00:59:39,973 --> 00:59:42,976
When she tried to tell somebody
about it, he brought her here.

899
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:44,311
I want more juice.

900
00:59:44,394 --> 00:59:45,604
And that one?

901
00:59:45,646 --> 00:59:46,980
Put your tray
back where it belongs.

902
00:59:47,064 --> 00:59:51,276
The police beat the crap out of
her brother, broke both his arms.

903
00:59:51,360 --> 00:59:53,821
When she tried to
tell the papers...

904
00:59:56,365 --> 00:59:57,616
And you?

905
00:59:58,826 --> 01:00:01,787
I work nights.

906
01:00:02,329 --> 01:00:03,831
Sure.

907
01:00:04,748 --> 01:00:08,043
I mean, I work nights.

908
01:00:09,837 --> 01:00:10,921
Oh.

909
01:00:11,004 --> 01:00:12,131
Yeah. In the clubs.
Downtown.

910
01:00:12,214 --> 01:00:13,298
I'm sorry.

911
01:00:13,340 --> 01:00:17,177
Yeah, well, this one client just
kept hitting me and he wouldn't stop,

912
01:00:17,219 --> 01:00:19,304
so I filed a complaint.

913
01:00:19,346 --> 01:00:21,849
And it turns out
he was a cop.

914
01:00:21,890 --> 01:00:24,016
Next thing I know,
I'm here.

915
01:00:24,767 --> 01:00:26,811
But they can't do that.

916
01:00:26,853 --> 01:00:27,937
Are you kidding?

917
01:00:28,020 --> 01:00:29,522
All right, one
more and then that's it.

918
01:00:29,605 --> 01:00:32,066
Everybody knows
women are fragile.

919
01:00:32,525 --> 01:00:35,403
I mean, they're all emotions, no logic,
there's nothing going on upstairs.

920
01:00:35,486 --> 01:00:37,071
Somebody! Help me!

921
01:00:37,155 --> 01:00:39,824
Every once in a while they say
something that's a little inconvenient,

922
01:00:39,866 --> 01:00:41,451
they just go fucking nuts.

923
01:00:41,534 --> 01:00:42,660
Pardon my French.

924
01:00:42,702 --> 01:00:44,454
You gotta get those dishes. You got it.

925
01:00:44,537 --> 01:00:48,249
If we're insane, nobody
has to listen to us.

926
01:00:49,459 --> 01:00:51,085
I mean, who are
you gonna believe,

927
01:00:51,169 --> 01:00:54,505
some crazy woman trying to
destroy the integrity of the force,

928
01:00:54,547 --> 01:00:56,340
or a police officer?

929
01:00:58,050 --> 01:01:01,095
Then once they get us in here, we
either shut up and we learn to behave,

930
01:01:01,179 --> 01:01:02,847
or we don't go home.

931
01:01:02,889 --> 01:01:04,515
Are you all done?

932
01:01:05,808 --> 01:01:07,769
Or we go home like that.

933
01:01:44,471 --> 01:01:47,933
Stop. Stop it.

934
01:01:48,809 --> 01:01:51,061
Stop it!
Stop it.

935
01:01:51,186 --> 01:01:52,395
Please.

936
01:01:55,107 --> 01:01:56,233
Clark.

937
01:01:57,275 --> 01:01:58,777
Sanford Clark?

938
01:01:59,611 --> 01:02:00,737
Here.

939
01:02:01,738 --> 01:02:03,782
Paperwork's come through.

940
01:02:03,865 --> 01:02:06,284
You'll be deported back to
Canada day after tomorrow.

941
01:02:06,368 --> 01:02:08,620
Police there will decide
what to do with you next.

942
01:02:08,703 --> 01:02:11,997
I hope your stay here has convinced
you not to try crossing the border

943
01:02:12,081 --> 01:02:13,833
illegally in the future.

944
01:02:13,958 --> 01:02:15,084
Wait!

945
01:02:17,211 --> 01:02:20,423
I'd like to talk to the
officer who brought me in.

946
01:02:20,506 --> 01:02:22,299
I'm sure he has far
more important things...

947
01:02:22,383 --> 01:02:24,677
Please. It's important.

948
01:02:31,517 --> 01:02:33,185
Christine Collins.

949
01:02:33,269 --> 01:02:35,938
Thank you. Mrs. Collins.

950
01:02:37,690 --> 01:02:40,443
Dr. Jonathan Steele.
Please, have a seat.

951
01:02:48,159 --> 01:02:51,495
I hope your stay with us
has been comfortable so far.

952
01:02:52,455 --> 01:02:53,581
Yes.

953
01:02:54,081 --> 01:02:55,541
Really?

954
01:02:55,666 --> 01:02:59,128
I'd think it'd
be quite difficult at first.

955
01:03:01,756 --> 01:03:02,964
Yes, it was.

956
01:03:03,006 --> 01:03:06,843
Of course it was very difficult,
but comfortable enough.

957
01:03:17,145 --> 01:03:20,523
I see that they have...
They've taken a blood test.

958
01:03:21,775 --> 01:03:23,526
The Wassermman Test.

959
01:03:23,610 --> 01:03:27,739
They said it was to check for
syphilis, 'cause it affects the mind.

960
01:03:27,864 --> 01:03:31,659
The idea that someone thinks you
need to be checked for syphilis,

961
01:03:31,701 --> 01:03:33,578
does that upset you?

962
01:03:33,661 --> 01:03:35,997
No, they said it was standard
procedure, so it did not.

963
01:03:36,039 --> 01:03:38,458
Yes, exactly.
Standard procedure.

964
01:03:38,541 --> 01:03:40,376
We have to cover
all our bases.

965
01:03:40,460 --> 01:03:41,878
I can imagine

966
01:03:44,214 --> 01:03:46,841
that for some people that
would be uncomfortable,

967
01:03:46,925 --> 01:03:49,094
but I understood.

968
01:04:07,611 --> 01:04:12,950
According to your file you
believe that the police substituted

969
01:04:13,075 --> 01:04:15,160
a fake boy for your son.

970
01:04:15,244 --> 01:04:17,413
No, I didn't say
he was a fake boy.

971
01:04:17,496 --> 01:04:19,581
He's not my boy.

972
01:04:19,665 --> 01:04:21,083
They brought home
the wrong boy.

973
01:04:21,166 --> 01:04:23,127
My son is still missing.

974
01:04:23,335 --> 01:04:28,215
Well, that's strange, because
I have here a newspaper article

975
01:04:28,674 --> 01:04:34,179
with a photo of you at the train
station, welcoming home your son.

976
01:04:37,057 --> 01:04:39,226
That is you in the
photo, isn't it?

977
01:04:39,810 --> 01:04:40,853
Yes.

978
01:04:40,936 --> 01:04:42,020
Yeah.

979
01:04:42,729 --> 01:04:43,730
Yes.

980
01:04:43,814 --> 01:04:46,775
So, at first
he was your son,

981
01:04:48,277 --> 01:04:50,069
and now he's not your son.

982
01:04:52,029 --> 01:04:53,948
Has this been going
on for a long time?

983
01:04:53,990 --> 01:04:57,618
People changing, becoming
something other than what they are?

984
01:04:57,702 --> 01:04:59,579
People don't change.

985
01:04:59,620 --> 01:05:01,205
You don't think
people change?

986
01:05:01,289 --> 01:05:02,373
No, that's not...

987
01:05:06,002 --> 01:05:08,254
The police, they're not
out to persecute you?

988
01:05:08,337 --> 01:05:10,715
No, they're not.

989
01:05:10,798 --> 01:05:13,885
The police are here
to protect you.

990
01:05:14,635 --> 01:05:15,928
Yes.

991
01:05:16,137 --> 01:05:17,597
Really?

992
01:05:17,638 --> 01:05:18,723
Yes.

993
01:05:19,807 --> 01:05:24,145
Well, that's odd because
when you were admitted,

994
01:05:25,146 --> 01:05:31,360
you told the head nurse that the police
were conspiring deliberately to punish you.

995
01:05:31,486 --> 01:05:35,907
