No.

1340
01:27:13,096 --> 01:27:14,639
You're free to leave.

1341
01:27:18,059 --> 01:27:19,143
What?

1342
01:27:19,519 --> 01:27:23,022
Your clothes are in the next
room. You can change there.

1343
01:27:23,773 --> 01:27:24,774
In the next room?

1344
01:27:24,857 --> 01:27:26,484
Yes. That's right.

1345
01:27:27,527 --> 01:27:28,820
See to it.

1346
01:27:33,866 --> 01:27:35,034
Christ.

1347
01:27:35,535 --> 01:27:36,577
Long as
it's not the original.

1348
01:27:36,661 --> 01:27:37,704
No, it's not.

1349
01:27:37,787 --> 01:27:39,163
Here it is.

1350
01:27:39,247 --> 01:27:41,082
And who is that? Is that
Baker's file or Larson?

1351
01:27:41,165 --> 01:27:42,375
That's Baker.

1352
01:27:42,458 --> 01:27:44,335
He said he wanted...

1353
01:27:44,377 --> 01:27:45,795
Nurse, I wanna see

1354
01:27:45,837 --> 01:27:48,965
every piece of paper you have on
the case of Mrs. Christine Collins,

1355
01:27:49,048 --> 01:27:51,050
and I want to see it right
now, do you understand me?

1356
01:27:51,134 --> 01:27:53,761
Every piece. When
will she be coming out?

1357
01:27:54,804 --> 01:27:55,804
Oh, it's just up ahead.

1358
01:27:55,887 --> 01:27:57,180
Oh, all right.
Let's...

1359
01:27:57,264 --> 01:27:59,516
Hurricane hits
West Palm Beach!

1360
01:27:59,558 --> 01:28:02,018
Babe Ruth hits
53rd home run!

1361
01:28:03,019 --> 01:28:04,980
Kids found murdered in
Riverside! There it is.

1362
01:28:05,063 --> 01:28:07,941
Biggest crime
in Los Angeles history!

1363
01:28:08,024 --> 01:28:10,068
Collins boy assumed dead!

1364
01:28:11,278 --> 01:28:13,780
Read it here!
Read it here!

1365
01:28:19,077 --> 01:28:21,163
Mrs. Collins,
I'm so sorry.

1366
01:28:25,625 --> 01:28:27,878
Captain, your handling of
the Christine Collins case

1367
01:28:27,961 --> 01:28:31,006
has exposed this department
to public ridicule.

1368
01:28:31,631 --> 01:28:35,427
There is even the possibility
of civil and criminal liability.

1369
01:28:35,886 --> 01:28:38,764
Sir, nobody could've known what
was happening up at that ranch.

1370
01:28:38,847 --> 01:28:41,892
Not us, the sheriff's department,
or the marshal's office.

1371
01:28:41,975 --> 01:28:44,061
And as for the
Collins woman,

1372
01:28:44,144 --> 01:28:46,897
I'm still not convinced that her boy
is among the victims up in Wineville.

1373
01:28:47,064 --> 01:28:48,148
No?

1374
01:28:48,231 --> 01:28:49,190
No.

1375
01:28:49,231 --> 01:28:52,735
There were four other photos of
missing boys that looked a lot like him.

1376
01:28:52,818 --> 01:28:54,737
The Clark kid
could've been mistaken.

1377
01:28:54,820 --> 01:28:56,155
Maybe he was.

1378
01:28:56,238 --> 01:28:59,450
Which begs the obvious
question. Who cares?

1379
01:29:00,868 --> 01:29:01,952
Sir?

1380
01:29:02,203 --> 01:29:04,372
The mayor wants
this to go away.

1381
01:29:04,455 --> 01:29:06,540
I want this to go away.

1382
01:29:06,624 --> 01:29:10,127
The way you do that is to stop
insisting that Walter Collins

1383
01:29:10,211 --> 01:29:12,713
is not among those boys killed
up at that goddamn ranch.

1384
01:29:12,797 --> 01:29:15,383
Because if the boy you brought
back is not Walter Collins,

1385
01:29:15,424 --> 01:29:18,427
and he's not dead up at that
ranch, then where the hell is he?

1386
01:29:18,511 --> 01:29:20,221
People are gonna want to
know why we haven't found him.

1387
01:29:20,262 --> 01:29:22,556
Why we're not
doing our job.

1388
01:29:23,265 --> 01:29:25,351
But if, on the other hand,

1389
01:29:25,434 --> 01:29:29,688
he is, or could be, among those
poor boys killed up in Wineville,

1390
01:29:30,147 --> 01:29:32,483
then the inquiries stop.

1391
01:29:34,235 --> 01:29:35,778
It's a momentary
embarrassment

1392
01:29:35,861 --> 01:29:37,988
you're just gonna
have to live with.

1393
01:29:38,072 --> 01:29:39,532
Better a short
inconvenience

1394
01:29:39,615 --> 01:29:42,742
than a lingering problem,
wouldn't you say, Captain?

1395
01:29:42,826 --> 01:29:43,993
Yes, sir.

1396
01:29:44,077 --> 01:29:45,954
The boy's been gone
nearly a year.

1397
01:29:45,995 --> 01:29:49,165
If he was going to be found,
it would've happened by now.

1398
01:29:49,249 --> 01:29:50,625
Whether he was up
at that ranch or not,

1399
01:29:50,667 --> 01:29:52,877
the truth is he probably
is dead somewhere.

1400
01:29:52,961 --> 01:29:57,006
Better his mother accept that
now than later, don't you think?

1401
01:29:57,090 --> 01:29:59,092
Yes, sir.
Good.

1402
01:29:59,134 --> 01:30:00,760
That'll be all, Captain.

1403
01:30:02,470 --> 01:30:06,141
That's how you want it,
then I guess we're done here.

1404
01:30:06,349 --> 01:30:08,017
Tell county jail we're
remanding him for trial.

1405
01:30:08,101 --> 01:30:11,980
Wait. I didn't do anything. I
wasn't even here when it happened.

1406
01:30:13,148 --> 01:30:14,482
By pretending to
be Walter Collins,

1407
01:30:14,566 --> 01:30:18,069
you're interfering in a police
investigation of a kidnapping and murder.

1408
01:30:18,153 --> 01:30:21,114
We can try you as accomplice
to that murder after the fact.

1409
01:30:21,197 --> 01:30:22,657
That's too bad.

1410
01:30:22,699 --> 01:30:26,453
County jail is a lot worse than
a juvenile hall or a foster home.

1411
01:30:26,494 --> 01:30:27,912
It's a lot worse.

1412
01:30:29,914 --> 01:30:32,417
You can't do that.
I'm just a kid.

1413
01:30:34,919 --> 01:30:36,962
Sanford Clark's a kid, too.

1414
01:30:37,004 --> 01:30:39,506
Fifteen.
He's going to jail.

1415
01:30:39,548 --> 01:30:43,761
All murderers and their accomplices
go to jail. Everybody knows that.

1416
01:30:45,929 --> 01:30:48,682
Get him out of here.
It's out of my hands now.

1417
01:30:48,724 --> 01:30:51,268
Wait. I don't
want to go to jail.

1418
01:31:01,528 --> 01:31:02,780
Prove it.

1419
01:31:04,448 --> 01:31:05,741
I...

1420
01:31:05,866 --> 01:31:09,411
I knew Los Angeles is where
they make the Tom Mix movies.

1421
01:31:10,079 --> 01:31:11,997
I figured
if I could meet Tom Mix

1422
01:31:12,039 --> 01:31:14,750
maybe he would let me
ride on his horse.

1423
01:31:16,293 --> 01:31:18,837
His horse is named Tony.
Did you know that?

1424
01:31:23,175 --> 01:31:24,551
How are you feeling?

1425
01:31:24,635 --> 01:31:26,011
All right.

1426
01:31:26,720 --> 01:31:28,472
The police still
have a car outside.

1427
01:31:28,555 --> 01:31:32,392
I guess they're waiting to see
what your next move is going to be.

1428
01:31:33,559 --> 01:31:35,561
I'm going home.
And then?

1429
01:31:36,062 --> 01:31:37,980
Then, I've been giving it
a lot of thought.

1430
01:31:38,064 --> 01:31:42,527
And what they did to those women,
and what they did about Walter.

1431
01:31:43,403 --> 01:31:47,073
I used to always tell him, "You never
start a fight, but you always finish it. "

1432
01:31:47,156 --> 01:31:50,576
And I didn't start this
fight, but I'm gonna finish it.

1433
01:31:51,160 --> 01:31:55,373
Mrs. Collins, right now you're a
sufficiently high profile that I think

1434
01:31:55,415 --> 01:31:59,252
even the police would hesitate
to go after you out in the open,

1435
01:31:59,752 --> 01:32:02,130
but I have to warn you that
could change very quickly

1436
01:32:02,213 --> 01:32:04,882
if they feel their
position threatened.

1437
01:32:04,966 --> 01:32:06,759
Very quickly indeed.

1438
01:32:08,136 --> 01:32:10,471
What are they gonna
do to me now?

1439
01:32:12,390 --> 01:32:14,016
They got nothing.

1440
01:32:17,019 --> 01:32:18,563
I'm going home.

1441
01:32:42,294 --> 01:32:43,670
Hi, sis.

1442
01:32:44,421 --> 01:32:45,756
Gordon.

1443
01:32:45,797 --> 01:32:48,300
I didn't know
you were back in town.

1444
01:32:48,967 --> 01:32:51,136
Yeah, I got in
a couple of days ago,

1445
01:32:51,219 --> 01:32:54,097
figured I'd surprise you.
Is that... Is that okay?

1446
01:32:54,139 --> 01:32:57,184
Yes. Yes, of course.
Of course, come on in.

1447
01:33:00,103 --> 01:33:02,397
Where's that
little niece of mine?

1448
01:33:02,481 --> 01:33:04,608
She went into town.

1449
01:33:04,649 --> 01:33:06,151
Should be back this evening.

1450
01:33:06,234 --> 01:33:07,444
Uh, Bob's here.

1451
01:33:07,486 --> 01:33:08,570
Oh, good.

1452
01:33:08,653 --> 01:33:10,989
Uh, I was gonna ask if I
could stay on a couple days.

1453
01:33:11,031 --> 01:33:12,407
Staying?

1454
01:33:12,824 --> 01:33:13,950
Yeah.

1455
01:33:13,992 --> 01:33:16,285
Listen, can I use
your bathroom?

1456
01:33:16,327 --> 01:33:18,329
It's been a long ride and
I could really use a shower.

1457
01:33:18,412 --> 01:33:20,331
Of course.
Okay.

1458
01:33:21,123 --> 01:33:22,500
Thank you.

1459
01:33:36,847 --> 01:33:38,099
Is that...

1460
01:33:38,307 --> 01:33:41,685
All right, go next door.
I'll call the police. Hurry.

1461
01:33:46,440 --> 01:33:48,150
<i>Operator.
How may I connect you?</i>

1462
01:33:48,693 --> 01:33:49,777
He's upstairs, sir.

1463
01:33:49,860 --> 01:33:52,613
Go around the other side!
Cut him off!

1464
01:33:52,697 --> 01:33:53,739
Come with me!
Yes, sir.

1465
01:33:53,823 --> 01:33:55,116
Let's go!

1466
01:33:59,286 --> 01:34:03,165
Mrs. Collins, I'd like you
to meet my friend, Mr. Hahn.

1467
01:34:03,207 --> 01:34:06,836
Mrs. Collins, my deepest
condolences on your loss.

1468
01:34:07,545 --> 01:34:09,087
May we come in?

1469
01:34:13,216 --> 01:34:15,093
I appreciate the sentiment,

1470
01:34:15,176 --> 01:34:17,387
but they've yet to find...

1471
01:34:17,470 --> 01:34:20,014
To identify the
remains as my son.

1472
01:34:22,183 --> 01:34:24,686
I'm afraid it never
gets any easier.

1473
01:34:25,228 --> 01:34:27,397
I lost a daughter
to polio five years ago.

1474
01:34:27,480 --> 01:34:29,691
There's not a day goes by
when I don't think,

1475
01:34:29,733 --> 01:34:32,277
"I should mention
this to Claudine. "

1476
01:34:32,360 --> 01:34:34,738
Then I remember
she's not here.

1477
01:34:37,574 --> 01:34:38,908
Please, sit.

1478
01:34:43,830 --> 01:34:45,749
I've been on the phone
all morning

1479
01:34:45,832 --> 01:34:49,044
with the appointment secretary
of the police commission.

1480
01:34:49,085 --> 01:34:51,087
