1482
01:34:54,466 --> 01:34:57,052
I know. My sources say
the police commission

1483
01:34:57,135 --> 01:35:01,222
is going to say that Jones and the
LAPD did absolutely nothing wrong,

1484
01:35:01,347 --> 01:35:04,391
and that the real blame lies
with the kid and with you

1485
01:35:04,475 --> 01:35:09,438
for being difficult and forcing them
to put you away for your own safety.

1486
01:35:12,775 --> 01:35:16,945
Then I guess I would have to
hire a lawyer, file a civil suit.

1487
01:35:17,738 --> 01:35:19,656
I went to the best
attorney in town,

1488
01:35:19,740 --> 01:35:22,576
a man who's sued this
city four times and won.

1489
01:35:22,618 --> 01:35:25,621
Unfortunately, we can't
afford to really hire him.

1490
01:35:25,662 --> 01:35:26,914
I see.

1491
01:35:26,955 --> 01:35:29,458
Which is why
I'm doing this pro bono.

1492
01:35:30,000 --> 01:35:33,337
It would be my honor to defend
your honor, Mrs. Collins.

1493
01:35:33,545 --> 01:35:34,922
In my 15 years as a lawyer,

1494
01:35:34,963 --> 01:35:38,801
I have never seen anyone fight
as long or as hard as you have,

1495
01:35:39,009 --> 01:35:42,179
in what is so clearly
in the cause of justice.

1496
01:35:42,971 --> 01:35:44,306
Thank you.

1497
01:35:44,890 --> 01:35:46,266
Let me see
what's on the shelf.

1498
01:35:46,308 --> 01:35:47,643
I'll look.

1499
01:35:49,728 --> 01:35:50,813
Yes? May I...

1500
01:35:50,896 --> 01:35:52,231
My name is S.S. Hahn,

1501
01:35:52,314 --> 01:35:55,150
and I have a court order for the immediate
release of all women being detained

1502
01:35:55,192 --> 01:35:58,152
in this institution under
the designation code 12

1503
01:35:58,194 --> 01:36:01,447
pending a formal inquiry into
the reasons for their detainment.

1504
01:36:01,489 --> 01:36:03,658
I'm sorry, the doctor
in charge is not here

1505
01:36:03,741 --> 01:36:05,284
until the morning.
Madam, let me be clearer.

1506
01:36:05,326 --> 01:36:08,121
Either you will produce the
people named in that court order,

1507
01:36:08,162 --> 01:36:11,749
or you will find yourself behind
bars, and I mean without a key.

1508
01:36:11,833 --> 01:36:14,961
I can't authorize you...
Madam, stand aside.

1509
01:36:24,929 --> 01:36:25,972
Can I see her now?

1510
01:36:26,055 --> 01:36:28,099
Sure. Absolutely.
How does she look?

1511
01:36:53,707 --> 01:36:55,709
All right, fellas, step
back. Let's give him room.

1512
01:36:55,751 --> 01:36:56,793
Here he is.

1513
01:36:56,877 --> 01:36:58,837
Mr. Northcott,
any comment on your arrest?

1514
01:36:58,920 --> 01:37:00,088
Mr. Northcott,
how are you feeling?

1515
01:37:00,172 --> 01:37:01,840
Oh, I'm feeling fine.

1516
01:37:01,882 --> 01:37:04,426
I've been on a little
vacation, as some of you know.

1517
01:37:04,509 --> 01:37:07,179
It was
a really pleasant vacation.

1518
01:37:07,262 --> 01:37:10,515
The police have certainly provided
me with a lot of amusement.

1519
01:37:10,557 --> 01:37:12,017
How long
you been in hiding?

1520
01:37:12,059 --> 01:37:13,351
How did you
avoid capture?

1521
01:37:13,393 --> 01:37:14,686
Easy, easy.
That's far enough.

1522
01:37:14,728 --> 01:37:16,438
Well, I didn't, did I?

1523
01:37:16,521 --> 01:37:17,606
One more shot!

1524
01:37:17,689 --> 01:37:19,649
Have you seen
your picture in the paper?

1525
01:37:19,733 --> 01:37:22,944
Didn't know anybody wanted
me until just recently.

1526
01:37:23,028 --> 01:37:24,613
Didn't even try.

1527
01:37:25,238 --> 01:37:28,283
My luggage still has
my initials on it, fellas.

1528
01:37:28,367 --> 01:37:30,494
Did you know why
the police were after you?

1529
01:37:30,577 --> 01:37:33,455
No, but I figured it'd be a good
idea if I were to just stay out of it.

1530
01:37:33,538 --> 01:37:34,539
Any remorse, sir?

1531
01:37:34,623 --> 01:37:39,336
Do you have anything to say to the
parents of the children you murdered?

1532
01:37:39,419 --> 01:37:41,088
No comment.

1533
01:37:41,171 --> 01:37:42,255
One more shot,
this way!

1534
01:37:43,881 --> 01:37:46,550
Mayor Cryer.
This is unexpected.

1535
01:37:47,426 --> 01:37:48,928
So was this.

1536
01:37:49,011 --> 01:37:52,431
Subpoenas, requests for
depositions, interrogatories.

1537
01:37:52,515 --> 01:37:56,102
All courtesy of Mr. Hahn and his
new client, Christine Collins.

1538
01:37:57,061 --> 01:37:58,604
You don't have to look them
over too closely, Chief.

1539
01:37:58,688 --> 01:38:01,440
Your own copies should
be coming any time now.

1540
01:38:01,524 --> 01:38:03,943
The city council has also
agreed to look into this,

1541
01:38:04,026 --> 01:38:05,069
starting immediately.

1542
01:38:05,152 --> 01:38:06,237
God damn it!

1543
01:38:06,278 --> 01:38:09,031
I thought this was
supposed to go away.

1544
01:38:09,657 --> 01:38:10,908
This is an election year.

1545
01:38:10,950 --> 01:38:12,451
I can't afford
this kind of press.

1546
01:38:12,535 --> 01:38:15,788
It is going away, sir. I've instructed
Captain Jones to deal with it.

1547
01:38:15,830 --> 01:38:17,415
I'm afraid,
falling on his sword

1548
01:38:17,456 --> 01:38:21,377
and saying he made a mistake isn't
going to be good enough, Chief.

1549
01:38:21,460 --> 01:38:24,922
If we take him out of
the picture for a while,

1550
01:38:24,964 --> 01:38:28,801
just might help calm things down
until the hearing's finished.

1551
01:38:46,443 --> 01:38:48,737
What is happening?
Didn't you hear?

1552
01:38:48,820 --> 01:38:50,572
It's the biggest protest
I've ever seen.

1553
01:38:50,655 --> 01:38:51,906
Protest?
Yeah.

1554
01:38:51,990 --> 01:38:55,160
Over the Collins broad,
if you can believe that.

1555
01:39:04,753 --> 01:39:07,922
We want justice!
We want justice!

1556
01:39:10,341 --> 01:39:11,926
Oh, my!

1557
01:39:18,391 --> 01:39:20,352
Mr. Harris.

1558
01:39:20,435 --> 01:39:23,730
The Lord works in mysterious
ways, Mrs. Collins.

1559
01:39:24,981 --> 01:39:26,858
Boy, does he ever.

1560
01:39:44,124 --> 01:39:46,710
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, can I
have your attention, please?</i>

1561
01:39:46,794 --> 01:39:51,340
There are more people gathered in this chamber
than have ever been in this room before.

1562
01:39:51,423 --> 01:39:55,135
Therefore, I ask you to refrain
from demonstrations of any kind.

1563
01:39:55,219 --> 01:39:56,678
Tell the truth!
Tell the truth!

1564
01:39:56,762 --> 01:40:00,683
We are all here because we want to
know the real facts in this case.

1565
01:40:00,724 --> 01:40:04,853
And everybody is going to be heard
if we have to sit here for a week.

1566
01:40:04,937 --> 01:40:07,856
Mr. Thorpe, I don't see any
members of the police commission.

1567
01:40:11,360 --> 01:40:14,530
Are there any members of the
police department in the room?

1568
01:40:14,571 --> 01:40:16,448
Is Chief Davis here?

1569
01:40:17,866 --> 01:40:19,451
Is Captain Jones here?

1570
01:40:21,245 --> 01:40:22,620
Is there anybody here
representing the police?

1571
01:40:22,704 --> 01:40:26,874
Mrs. Collins, could you come across
the street with me for just a moment?

1572
01:40:26,958 --> 01:40:29,168
There's something
I think you should see.

1573
01:40:29,252 --> 01:40:31,254
Well, I hate to call a recess
before we've even started,

1574
01:40:31,337 --> 01:40:32,880
but I think a few
phone calls are in order.

1575
01:40:37,093 --> 01:40:40,012
The police decided it'd be best
to keep this off the main docket

1576
01:40:40,096 --> 01:40:44,350
in order to avoid exactly the sort
of chaos we have across the street.

1577
01:40:56,988 --> 01:40:59,949
Mrs. Collins.
I'm Leanne Clay.

1578
01:41:00,783 --> 01:41:03,036
This is my husband, John.
Hi.

1579
01:41:03,953 --> 01:41:06,956
I just wanted to pass
along my sympathies.

1580
01:41:07,248 --> 01:41:09,375
What we went through
waiting to hear anything

1581
01:41:09,459 --> 01:41:13,588
about our son David
was bad enough, now this.

1582
01:41:14,505 --> 01:41:18,467
But what the police did to
you, there was no call for that.

1583
01:41:18,550 --> 01:41:20,093
No call at all.

1584
01:41:23,138 --> 01:41:24,681
All rise.

1585
01:41:33,440 --> 01:41:35,442
Please, be seated.
Bailiff.

1586
01:41:48,705 --> 01:41:49,915
Oh, hey.

1587
01:41:52,125 --> 01:41:54,252
I saw you in the papers.

1588
01:41:54,336 --> 01:41:58,173
You got a lot of moxie, standing
up to the police like that.

1589
01:42:03,387 --> 01:42:05,347
The defendant
will please rise.

1590
01:42:10,976 --> 01:42:13,062
Gordon Stewart Northcott,

1591
01:42:13,145 --> 01:42:17,316
you've been charged with three
counts of murder in the first degree,

1592
01:42:17,358 --> 01:42:22,071
with an additional 17 counts under
review by the district attorney's office.

1593
01:42:22,154 --> 01:42:23,781
How do you plea?

1594
01:42:25,199 --> 01:42:27,326
Oh, not guilty, Your Honor.

1595
01:42:31,080 --> 01:42:33,249
You may sit, Mr. Northcott.

1596
01:42:37,837 --> 01:42:42,758
In light of the defendant's penchant for
international travel, no bail will be set.

1597
01:42:42,842 --> 01:42:45,428
This court will hear preliminary
motions by tomorrow morning.

1598
01:42:45,511 --> 01:42:47,972
The boy,
Walter Collins,

1599
01:42:48,055 --> 01:42:50,808
was reported as missing,
March 10, 1928.

1600
01:42:51,600 --> 01:42:54,228
We then instituted
a nationwide search.

1601
01:42:54,311 --> 01:42:58,232
On August 18th, we received
a cable indicating that a boy

1602
01:42:58,315 --> 01:43:01,736
matching his description was
found in DeKalb, Illinois.

1603
01:43:01,819 --> 01:43:05,864
Upon questioning, he admitted
to being Walter Collins.

1604
01:43:05,905 --> 01:43:10,869
We then made arrangements for him
to be transported back to California.

1605
01:43:11,119 --> 01:43:13,580
Where Mrs. Collins told you
the boy was not her son.

1606
01:43:13,663 --> 01:43:15,415
Yes. She denied
his identity

1607
01:43:15,498 --> 01:43:18,501
in spite of all of the evidence
pointing to the contrary.

1608
01:43:18,585 --> 01:43:21,671
But, as subsequent
events have demonstrated,

1609
01:43:21,755 --> 01:43:23,423
she was correct.

1610
01:43:24,674 --> 01:43:26,551
So, what prompted
you to send her

1611
01:43:26,593 --> 01:43:28,219
for psychological
evaluation?

1612
01:43:28,303 --> 01:43:30,055
Whether or not this was
in fact the correct boy

1613
01:43:30,096 --> 01:43:32,640
was not relevant
to my decision.

1614
01:43:32,724 --> 01:43:34,893
Throughout this period,
she acted strangely.

1615
01:43:34,934 --> 01:43:38,480
She was often cool
and aloof and unemotional,

1616
01:43:38,563 --> 01:43:42,233
especially when confronted
with the boy we found in DeKalb

1617
01:43:42,275 --> 01:43:44,361
and in our
subsequent conversation.

1618
01:43:44,444 --> 01:43:46,279
It was because of her

1619
01:43:47,113 --> 01:43:51,785
disturbing behavior that I
submitted her for observation

1620
01:43:51,868 --> 01:43:54,662
to the psychopathic ward of Los
Angeles County General Hospital.

1621
01:43:54,746 --> 01:43:56,038
Just like that.

1622
01:43:56,121 --> 01:43:58,290
You snap your fingers
and an innocent woman

1623
01:43:58,374 --> 01:44:00,084
is thrown
into the psycho ward!

1624
01:44:00,125 --> 01:44:03,462
She wasn't thrown. Every family
in this state is in grave danger

1625
01:44:03,545 --> 01:44:06,673
when a police captain can
take a woman into his office

1626
01:44:06,799 --> 01:44:08,092
and five minutes later

1627
01:44:08,133 --> 01:44:10,886
have her thrown into the psychopathic
ward on his own authority!

1628
01:44:10,969 --> 01:44:12,346
She wasn't thrown.

1629
01:44:12,429 --> 01:44:15,766
She wasn't thrown!
She wasn't thrown!

1630
01:44:16,433 --> 01:44:18,310
What was that, Captain?

1631
01:44:18,936 --> 01:44:21,105
She wasn't thrown.
She was escorted.

1632
01:44:24,858 --> 01:44:28,404
Escorted, thrown, the verb
doesn't matter, Captain.

1633
01:44:28,487 --> 01:44:32,700
What does matter is that her incarceration
was ordered without a warrant.

1634
01:44:32,783 --> 01:44:34,702
I am holding a carbon copy

1635
01:44:34,785 --> 01:44:37,913
of the affidavit of insanity
that was issued in the case

1636
01:44:37,996 --> 01:44:41,417
<i>of the State of California
v. Christine Collins.</i>

1637
01:44:41,500 --> 01:44:42,960
Who signed the affidavit?

1638
01:44:43,001 --> 01:44:44,128
I did.

1639
01:44:44,169 --> 01:44:46,797
Well, now, let me see
if I have this correct,

1640
01:44:46,880 --> 01:44:50,466
a woman was thrown into the
psychopathic ward without a warrant,

1641
01:44:50,550 --> 01:44:52,719
because no warrant existed.

1642
01:44:52,802 --> 01:44:55,346
And when it was finally
written several days later,

1643
01:44:55,430 --> 01:44:57,807
there was no need to sign it
or to go to a judge

1644
01:44:57,849 --> 01:45:00,643
because she was already
in the asylum!

1645
01:45:02,311 --> 01:45:03,396
Is this correct, Captain?

1646
01:45:03,479 --> 01:45:04,731
Technically, yes.

1647
01:45:04,814 --> 01:45:07,817
Extraordinary steps were necessary
because we were dealing...

1648
01:45:07,900 --> 01:45:09,736
We were dealing with
an extraordinary situation.

1649
01:45:09,819 --> 01:45:12,488
Now, is it our fault
that we were being deceived

1650
01:45:12,572 --> 01:45:15,366
by a boy who claimed to
be Walter Collins? No.

1651
01:45:16,159 --> 01:45:19,162
In light of his claims
and her disturbing behavior,

1652
01:45:19,203 --> 01:45:21,831
who wouldn't begin to think that there
was something the matter with her?

1653
01:45:21,873 --> 01:45:22,915
Because she questioned you?

1654
01:45:22,999 --> 01:45:25,168
No, because
she wouldn't listen!

1655
01:45:25,251 --> 01:45:27,045
Because she insisted
on being obstinate!

1656
01:45:27,128 --> 01:45:30,339
Because she tried to take
matters into her own hand,

1657
01:45:30,423 --> 01:45:32,216
best left to
qualified officers!

1658
01:45:32,258 --> 01:45:33,968
Because once
civil disobedience starts...

1659
01:45:34,052 --> 01:45:36,095
Because she was fighting
for the life of her son!

1660
01:45:36,179 --> 01:45:38,181
A boy who may have
still been alive

1661
01:45:38,222 --> 01:45:42,893
while you were wasting valuable time
denying you had done anything wrong!

1662
01:45:45,645 --> 01:45:47,189
And in the end

1663
01:45:48,732 --> 01:45:51,443
that's what
happened, isn't it?

1664
01:45:51,568 --> 01:45:55,030
At some point, while
all this was going on,

1665
01:45:57,199 --> 01:45:59,868
Walter Collins
was brutally murdered,

1666
01:46:00,827 --> 01:46:03,246
along with as many
as 19 other boys

1667
01:46:05,040 --> 01:46:07,709
at the Northcott Ranch
in Wineville.

1668
01:46:09,503 --> 01:46:11,671
Is that correct, Captain?

1669
01:46:13,298 --> 01:46:14,800
Yes, it is.

1670
01:46:15,550 --> 01:46:17,177
It's a travesty.

1671
01:46:22,849 --> 01:46:24,685
No further questions.

1672
01:46:42,076 --> 01:46:44,078
<i>Train number 14,
now boarding on track...</i>

1673
01:46:44,120 --> 01:46:47,998
So, after much effort, we
were able to identify this boy,

1674
01:46:48,082 --> 01:46:50,626
who's been responsible
for so much trouble lately,

1675
01:46:50,710 --> 01:46:53,587
as Arthur Hutchins
of Cedar Rapids, Iowa.

1676
01:46:54,380 --> 01:46:57,633
Between this, and the arrest of
the man suspected of murdering

1677
01:46:57,717 --> 01:46:59,427
the real Walter Collins,

1678
01:46:59,510 --> 01:47:02,805
we've cleared up two of the biggest
mysteries in the history of Los Angeles.

1679
01:47:02,847 --> 01:47:05,057
I hope you gentlemen
of the press will give

1680
01:47:05,141 --> 01:47:07,184
as much space to the
good things we do

1681
01:47:07,268 --> 01:47:09,812
as the mistakes that are
made on rare occasions.

1682
01:47:09,895 --> 01:47:11,731
Gentlemen, allow me
to introduce you

1683
01:47:11,814 --> 01:47:14,859
to the boy's real mother,
Mrs. Janet Hutchins.

1684
01:47:16,318 --> 01:47:17,778
Arthur.

1685
01:47:17,862 --> 01:47:19,363
I hope he wasn't too
much trouble for you.

1686
01:47:19,447 --> 01:47:21,240
Oh, no, not at all.

1687
01:47:21,323 --> 01:47:23,492
How about
a photograph, fellas?

1688
01:47:26,579 --> 01:47:27,997
One more.

1689
01:47:28,539 --> 01:47:29,998
Mrs. Hutchins,

1690
01:47:30,040 --> 01:47:33,376
Mrs. Collins, the woman he was
staying with, wanted him to have these.

1691
01:47:33,460 --> 01:47:34,961
They're the clothes
she let him wear.

1692
01:47:35,003 --> 01:47:36,838
Well, thank you.

1693
01:47:36,880 --> 01:47:38,673
Isn't that nice, Arthur?

1694
01:47:38,715 --> 01:47:41,092
Tell the nice officer,
"Thank you. "

1695
01:47:41,176 --> 01:47:44,137
I don't want them.
Give them to somebody else.

1696
01:47:44,220 --> 01:47:45,847
Precocious
little fellow, isn't he?

1697
01:47:45,930 --> 01:47:48,224
It's not my fault.
It's the police.

1698
01:47:48,308 --> 01:47:51,936
They said I was Walter Collins,
not me! It wasn't my idea!

1699
01:47:52,020 --> 01:47:53,480
Not my idea!
Get...

1700
01:47:53,521 --> 01:47:55,982
Yeah. Go blame the police
for your own mistakes.

1701
01:47:56,024 --> 01:47:58,193
We've seen a lot of
that lately, haven't we?

1702
01:47:58,276 --> 01:48:01,196
Take care now, Arthur!
Safe travels.

1703
01:48:02,364 --> 01:48:04,616
All right, fellas,
that's it for today.

1704
01:48:04,699 --> 01:48:06,409
Sir, sir! What did the boy mean by that?

1705
01:48:06,701 --> 01:48:10,205
It was March 10th, and
I came home from work,

1706
01:48:10,288 --> 01:48:13,166
and my nine-year-old
son, Walter, was gone.

1707
01:48:13,208 --> 01:48:16,961
Captain Jones was acting on
information he believed to be correct.

1708
01:48:17,045 --> 01:48:20,674
Walter Collins had a diastema,
also known as a diastema.

1709
01:48:20,715 --> 01:48:22,258
That child was never
in my classroom.

1710
01:48:22,384 --> 01:48:23,884
I can certainly
attest to that.

1711
01:48:23,967 --> 01:48:27,346
We rely on our good friends
in the police department

1712
01:48:27,388 --> 01:48:30,474
to point to us those
people who exhibit behavior

1713
01:48:30,557 --> 01:48:33,268
which is socially
unacceptable.

1714
01:48:33,352 --> 01:48:38,190
About four inches shorter
than the last mark of Walter.

1715
01:48:39,066 --> 01:48:41,568
Well, some of
these pictures show

1716
01:48:41,652 --> 01:48:44,321
what Sanford Clark
told me,

1717
01:48:44,405 --> 01:48:47,991
that he did in fact help in
the murder of these children.

1718
01:48:48,075 --> 01:48:49,743
Thank you, Detective.

1719
01:48:49,827 --> 01:48:51,036
Gentlemen of the jury,

1720
01:48:51,120 --> 01:48:53,914
I ask you to take a good
look at these images.

1721
01:48:53,956 --> 01:48:56,542
They establish beyond
any reasonable doubt

1722
01:48:56,583 --> 01:49:00,379
the circumstances and the
nature of these heinous crimes.

1723
01:49:11,598 --> 01:49:13,475
I'm in here,
Reverend.

1724
01:49:21,607 --> 01:49:23,735
When Walter was here, I
used to walk by his room

1725
01:49:23,776 --> 01:49:25,945
when he was sleeping.

1726
01:49:26,029 --> 01:49:30,033
And even though I couldn't
see him or hear him,

1727
01:49:30,116 --> 01:49:31,826
I could feel him.

1728
01:49:34,078 --> 01:49:36,789
