02:07:21,918 --> 02:07:25,129
<i>...The Thin Man, Cleopatra...</i>

1977
02:07:25,213 --> 02:07:26,839
Overrated.

1978
02:07:26,923 --> 02:07:28,966
<i>...and It Happened One Night.</i>

1979
02:07:29,050 --> 02:07:31,010
Clark Gable,
Claudette Colbert.

1980
02:07:31,052 --> 02:07:32,470
I rest my case.

1981
02:07:32,512 --> 02:07:34,973
<i>May I have the
envelope, please?</i>

1982
02:07:36,599 --> 02:07:40,311
<i>And the winner is
It Happened One Night.</i>

1983
02:07:42,188 --> 02:07:44,399
I knew it! I knew it,
I knew it, I knew it!

1984
02:07:46,484 --> 02:07:48,111
Dinner is on me.

1985
02:07:48,194 --> 02:07:50,029
<i>Is this
Christine Collins?</i>

1986
02:07:50,113 --> 02:07:52,281
Yes, it is.

1987
02:07:52,365 --> 02:07:54,951
<i>This is Mrs. Clay.
Do you remember me?</i>

1988
02:07:55,576 --> 02:07:57,869
Mrs. Clay,
of course I remember you.

1989
02:07:57,953 --> 02:07:59,997
<i>I just had to
call you right off.</i>

1990
02:08:00,080 --> 02:08:02,332
<i>What is it?
The police just called.</i>

1991
02:08:02,416 --> 02:08:04,626
<i>They found a boy,
Christine.</i>

1992
02:08:06,420 --> 02:08:08,547
<i>Where?
Lincoln Heights Precinct.</i>

1993
02:08:08,630 --> 02:08:10,090
<i>We're leaving right now.</i>

1994
02:08:10,173 --> 02:08:11,675
I'll be right down.

1995
02:08:34,364 --> 02:08:35,657
Oh, here.

1996
02:08:36,325 --> 02:08:37,701
I wanted to go
to him right off,

1997
02:08:37,743 --> 02:08:40,871
but they said it was important
to talk to him alone first.

1998
02:08:40,954 --> 02:08:43,081
Are they sure?
They're sure.

1999
02:08:43,165 --> 02:08:46,335
But, more important,
I'm sure.

2000
02:08:46,418 --> 02:08:47,502
It's my boy, all right.

2001
02:08:47,586 --> 02:08:49,420
It's David.

2002
02:08:49,462 --> 02:08:51,589
He's alive, Christine.

2003
02:08:51,672 --> 02:08:53,090
They found him
up in Hesperia.

2004
02:08:53,132 --> 02:08:56,135
<i>You were walking
home from school,</i>

2005
02:08:56,218 --> 02:08:58,387
<i>and they told you they
needed help finding a dog.</i>

2006
02:08:58,471 --> 02:08:59,722
<i>Yeah.</i>

2007
02:08:59,805 --> 02:09:02,892
<i>So, after you got in the
truck, what happened next?</i>

2008
02:09:02,933 --> 02:09:05,269
<i>They drove me around
for a long time,</i>

2009
02:09:05,311 --> 02:09:06,896
then we ended up
at this ranch.

2010
02:09:07,021 --> 02:09:10,441
Come on.
Come on, Davy.

2011
02:09:10,483 --> 02:09:11,859
Davy! Come on.
Get off me.

2012
02:09:11,942 --> 02:09:13,110
Don't fight
this much. Hey!

2013
02:09:13,194 --> 02:09:15,279
Were there other
boys there?

2014
02:09:15,988 --> 02:09:18,449
<i>Yeah. Five, I think.</i>

2015
02:09:20,034 --> 02:09:21,952
It was a long
time ago, though.

2016
02:09:22,036 --> 02:09:24,330
Hello, boys.
This is Davy.

2017
02:09:24,413 --> 02:09:25,790
I know you'll make
him feel... Hey!

2018
02:09:26,957 --> 02:09:30,294
No. No! Hey!
Shut up!

2019
02:09:30,336 --> 02:09:32,254
Did you speak to them?

2020
02:09:33,005 --> 02:09:35,591
Yeah? You remember
any of their names?

2021
02:09:36,467 --> 02:09:38,469
Yeah.

2022
02:09:38,511 --> 02:09:39,971
Two of them
were brothers.

2023
02:09:40,012 --> 02:09:42,847
I think their last
name was Winslow.

2024
02:09:44,140 --> 02:09:46,267
<i>The oldest one
was Jeffrey.</i>

2025
02:09:50,230 --> 02:09:51,731
And Walter.

2026
02:09:54,150 --> 02:09:55,652
<i>Walter?</i>

2027
02:09:56,444 --> 02:09:59,322
Yeah. Do you remember
Walter's last name?

2028
02:10:04,786 --> 02:10:06,037
Collins.

2029
02:10:07,706 --> 02:10:09,290
<i>Walter Collins.</i>

2030
02:10:10,333 --> 02:10:13,545
Tell me something if you only
remember some of the boys' names,

2031
02:10:13,628 --> 02:10:16,297
how come you remember his full name?

2032
02:10:17,007 --> 02:10:19,134
Because of
what happened.

2033
02:10:19,217 --> 02:10:21,261
<i>Walter and Jeffrey
were talking.</i>

2034
02:10:21,344 --> 02:10:23,263
<i>Pull it. They kept checking around</i>

2035
02:10:23,346 --> 02:10:25,932
and they found a part of the coop
where the wire was all messed up.

2036
02:10:26,016 --> 02:10:27,600
Be careful!

2037
02:10:27,684 --> 02:10:29,352
Hurry!

2038
02:10:29,436 --> 02:10:31,813
Maybe make enough room to
get out of there and run.

2039
02:10:31,855 --> 02:10:33,565
When we get
out, we split up,

2040
02:10:33,648 --> 02:10:35,400
go in different
directions. Okay?

2041
02:10:35,483 --> 02:10:37,568
They can't catch all of us.

2042
02:10:37,651 --> 02:10:39,611
It'd make an awful
lot of noise.

2043
02:10:39,695 --> 02:10:42,406
Be quiet. You got it?

2044
02:10:42,489 --> 02:10:45,367
And if it wasn't wide
enough, then we'd be stuck.

2045
02:10:48,746 --> 02:10:51,957
Wait. Help! Help!
Come on, hurry!

2046
02:10:52,875 --> 02:10:56,170
My foot's stuck! Hurry,
help! Help me, please!

2047
02:10:58,714 --> 02:11:01,592
He's coming!
He's...

2048
02:11:01,675 --> 02:11:03,344
My foot!

2049
02:11:04,261 --> 02:11:05,804
He's coming.

2050
02:11:05,888 --> 02:11:07,640
Hurry, run, run, run!

2051
02:11:12,728 --> 02:11:15,230
Hey! What
the hell are you boys...

2052
02:11:17,107 --> 02:11:21,737
Oh! Mary, Mother of
God! Hey! Hey! Hey!

2053
02:11:22,488 --> 02:11:25,532
You get back here!
Hey! Hold it! Hey!

2054
02:11:28,035 --> 02:11:29,119
Hey!

2055
02:11:30,286 --> 02:11:31,371
Hey!

2056
02:11:32,580 --> 02:11:34,207
Stop!

2057
02:11:36,542 --> 02:11:37,919
Check on the others!

2058
02:11:37,960 --> 02:11:39,379
Stop! Damn it!

2059
02:11:39,420 --> 02:11:41,714
Boys,
I'm coming after you!

2060
02:11:41,756 --> 02:11:44,884
Damn it! Damn it!

2061
02:11:45,176 --> 02:11:48,096
Boys, I'll find you no
matter where you are!

2062
02:11:48,179 --> 02:11:50,556
They're not in there!
Come on! Get in the car!

2063
02:11:50,598 --> 02:11:54,727
I'm gonna find you! Damn
it! Damn it! Come on.

2064
02:11:54,811 --> 02:11:57,230
Shit! Get in
the car, Sanford!

2065
02:12:04,696 --> 02:12:07,323
That was the last
I saw of any of them.

2066
02:12:07,907 --> 02:12:10,910
So, you don't know if either
of the other two were captured?

2067
02:12:10,994 --> 02:12:12,078
No.

2068
02:12:13,371 --> 02:12:15,289
All I know is,

2069
02:12:15,331 --> 02:12:18,209
if Walter hadn't
come back for me

2070
02:12:19,085 --> 02:12:21,796
<i>I don't think I ever
would've gotten out of there.</i>

2071
02:12:22,714 --> 02:12:24,089
Okay.

2072
02:12:25,340 --> 02:12:27,509
So, what happened
after that?

2073
02:12:27,592 --> 02:12:29,261
I kept off
the main roads,

2074
02:12:29,344 --> 02:12:34,308
until I saw a train stopped
at a crossing and I jumped in.

2075
02:12:34,725 --> 02:12:37,769
Why didn't you tell
anyone what had happened?

2076
02:12:37,853 --> 02:12:39,313
I was afraid.

2077
02:12:39,813 --> 02:12:42,816
I thought they'd come
after me, or my folks.

2078
02:12:44,609 --> 02:12:47,029
<i>So, I just didn't
tell anybody.</i>

2079
02:12:48,905 --> 02:12:53,118
I was on my own until I got a free
meal from this lady, Miss Lansing.

2080
02:12:53,160 --> 02:12:55,662
Told her I was an
orphan, on my own.

2081
02:12:57,664 --> 02:12:59,624
She said I could stay on.

2082
02:13:01,084 --> 02:13:02,419
And I did.

2083
02:13:03,670 --> 02:13:05,005
<i>Every night,</i>

2084
02:13:05,088 --> 02:13:08,508
I'd wake up thinking they
were right outside my window.

2085
02:13:09,051 --> 02:13:11,511
And then I heard the
police talking on the radio

2086
02:13:11,595 --> 02:13:14,348
about what happened
at the ranch.

2087
02:13:14,473 --> 02:13:16,849
And I thought, "For sure
I can't go back now. "

2088
02:13:16,891 --> 02:13:18,351
Why?

2089
02:13:18,893 --> 02:13:19,977
Why not?

2090
02:13:20,019 --> 02:13:22,813
Since I didn't tell
anybody what happened.

2091
02:13:24,190 --> 02:13:26,984
I was afraid they'd blame
me for those kids being dead.

2092
02:13:28,861 --> 02:13:30,738
So I just stayed away.

2093
02:13:32,490 --> 02:13:35,493
What made you come forward
now, after all this time?

2094
02:13:35,534 --> 02:13:38,120
Hmm? Why come
forward now?

2095
02:13:41,707 --> 02:13:43,459
I really miss my mom.

2096
02:13:45,878 --> 02:13:47,755
I really miss my dad.

2097
02:13:50,800 --> 02:13:52,760
I just wanna go home.

2098
02:13:56,180 --> 02:13:57,974
<i>I just wanna go home.</i>

2099
02:14:03,980 --> 02:14:05,731
Are you all right?

2100
02:14:06,399 --> 02:14:08,609
I love you.

2101
02:14:41,099 --> 02:14:42,892
I still can't believe it.

2102
02:14:42,934 --> 02:14:46,855
Five years, case closed, everyone
thinks he's dead, and there he is.

2103
02:14:48,356 --> 02:14:51,109
Wouldn't be, if it
wasn't for Walter.

2104
02:14:52,777 --> 02:14:55,363
Your son did a brave
thing, Mrs. Collins.

2105
02:14:55,447 --> 02:14:57,615
You should be
very proud of him.

2106
02:14:57,699 --> 02:14:59,034
I am.

2107
02:15:01,369 --> 02:15:02,911
You still think
he's out there?

2108
02:15:02,995 --> 02:15:04,246
Why not?

2109
02:15:05,456 --> 02:15:07,458
Three boys made a run for
it that night, Detective.

2110
02:15:07,499 --> 02:15:09,043
And if one got out,

2111
02:15:09,126 --> 02:15:12,212
then maybe either or both
of the others did, too.

2112
02:15:12,296 --> 02:15:15,841
Maybe Walter's out there, having
the same fears that he did.

2113
02:15:15,966 --> 02:15:17,801
Afraid to come home
and identify himself,

2114
02:15:17,885 --> 02:15:20,304
or afraid he'll get
into trouble.

2115
02:15:21,722 --> 02:15:23,807
But either way,

2116
02:15:23,891 --> 02:15:27,019
it gives me something I
didn't have before tonight.

2117
02:15:27,144 --> 02:15:28,520
What's that?

2118
02:15:29,480 --> 02:15:30,689
Hope.

